hopobject.body: There's a three month trial period vizhub.healthdata.org * Obama administration officials, scrambling to get thehealth law's insurance marketplaces ready to open on Tuesday,keep hitting technical problems, while government-funded fieldworkers across the country say they aren't fully prepared tohelp Americans enroll in the program. Implementation of the lawis expected to proceed even if the government partially shutsdown because Congress fails to pass the necessary spendingbills. ()
